@startuml data-flow
' Data flow through the DataPilot scoring engine, from indicator
' responses to the Global Maturity Index. Grounded in useAppStore.js.
' No em-dashes or en-dashes anywhere.

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #2E2E38
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam ArrowFontColor #2E2E38

skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #3D108A
  BackgroundColor #F0EEF8
  FontColor #2E2E38
  FontSize 13
  roundCorner 14
}
skinparam note {
  BorderColor #27ACAA
  BackgroundColor #E8F8F8
  FontColor #2E2E38
  FontSize 11
}

title Data Flow Through the DataPilot Scoring Engine

rectangle "Indicator raw score\n(scale 1 to 5, or skipped)" as RAW #F0EEF8
rectangle "getEffectiveScore()" as EFF #EDE7F6
rectangle "getSubDimScore()\naverage per sub-dimension" as SUB #E3F2FD
rectangle "getDimScore()\naverage of sub-dimension scores" as DIM #F0EEF8
rectangle "getGlobalScore()  GMI\nweighted 25/20/20/20/15,\nrenormalized over answered weights" as GMI #E8F8F8
rectangle "getPercentage()\nround(score x 20)" as PCT #E8F5E9
rectangle "getMaturityLevel()\nLevel 1 to Level 5" as LVL #E8F5E9
rectangle "Results screen\nGMI, maturity badge,\nradar chart, dimension bars" as RES #F0EEF8

RAW --> EFF
note right of EFF
  If skipped or unanswered the
  score is null and excluded.
  Evidence cap: if raw score >= 3
  with no evidence, effective
  score is set to 2.
end note

EFF --> SUB
note right of SUB
  Mean of the effective scores of
  its indicators, null values excluded.
end note

SUB --> DIM
note right of DIM
  Mean of its sub-dimension scores,
  null values excluded.
end note

DIM --> GMI
note right of GMI
  GMI = sum over answered dimensions of
  DimScore x (Weight / sum of answered weights).
  Rounded to two decimals.
  Worked example: GMI = 2.19 of 5.
end note

GMI --> PCT
GMI --> LVL
note right of LVL
  Bands: 1.00 to 1.79 Initial,
  1.80 to 2.59 Emerging,
  2.60 to 3.39 Defined,
  3.40 to 4.19 Managed,
  4.20 to 5.00 Optimized.
  2.19 falls in Level 2 Emerging.
end note
note right of PCT
  round(2.19 x 20) = 44 percent.
end note

PCT --> RES
LVL --> RES

@enduml
